    "Fair use is less likely to apply when works are created for the sole purpose of training machine learning models as in the case of supervised datasets with copyrightable compositions or annotations.",
    "Most literature on fair use and machine learning focuses on copyrighted art or text large part by non-commercial and synthetic datasets that are often generated by commercial APIs.",
    "a, Licence use categories versus text lengths (log-scaled character length).",
    "b, Synthetic and/or regular datasets versus text lengths (logscaled character length).).",
    "While the expressive purpose of a piece of text or art is not to train machine learning models, the purpose of a training dataset is to do just that."
